    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hot-honey-and-peanut-butter-wagyu-burger-with-black-pepper-chips/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crispy \u2013 these are your <strong>black pepper chips</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hot-honey-and-peanut-butter-wagyu-burger-with-black-pepper-chips/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Zest <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter), then cut in half</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hot-honey-and-peanut-butter-wagyu-burger-with-black-pepper-chips/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>slaw mix </strong>and <strong>lime zest </strong>to a bowl with a squeeze of <strong>lime juice</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>zesty slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hot-honey-and-peanut-butter-wagyu-burger-with-black-pepper-chips/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>honey </strong>and <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>hot honey</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>peanut butter </strong>to a separate small bowl with a splash of <strong>warm water </strong>and a squeeze of <strong>lime juice </strong>and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>peanut drizzle</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hot-honey-and-peanut-butter-wagyu-burger-with-black-pepper-chips/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chips have had 20 min, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>wagyu burger[s] </strong>and cook for 6 min on each side, or until nicely browned</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 5? You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hot-honey-and-peanut-butter-wagyu-burger-with-black-pepper-chips/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half (if required!)</p><p>Once everything is nearly ready, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>brioche halves</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To build the burger, top the <strong>warmed brioche bun base</strong> with a little <strong>zesty slaw </strong>and a <strong>wagyu patty</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>peanut drizzle </strong>and <strong>hot honey </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) evenly between the burgers and top with the<strong> warmed brioche bun lid</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>black pepper chips </strong>and the <strong>remaining slaw </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
